Wayne McCurrie from FNB Wealth & Investments chose CVS Health as his stock pick of the day and David Shapiro from Sasfin Securities chose L’Oreal. McCurrie said: “I’m going with an American company called CVS Health, a hospital health group and they came out with their results on Tuesday. Slightly disappointing results but their outlook is very, very good.” Shapiro said: “I’m going for L’Oreal, they have very good skincare products and coming on the back of some very good numbers, I think stay at home people, the return of the Asian markets has been pushing up the demand for skincare, particularly online.” Or listen to the full audio: Subscribe for free episodes: iono.fm | Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Pocket Casts | Player.fm